  "notes": "Lengadocian reference variety in the classical (Alibertine) norm. Key traits: unmarked o reads [u] (ó [u], ò [ɔ]); word-final unstressed a reads [ɔ]; u is fronted [y]; v merges with b (betacism); voiced stops lenite to approximants between vowels; word-final n and infinitive -r are silent. Substantial dialectal variation across Gascon, Provençal, Limousin, Auvergnat, and Vivaro-Alpine is not encoded here.",
