    "stress_mark": "ˈ",
    "notes": "Occitan classical (Alibertine) norm accentuation (Bec 1973, Alibert): final stress by default. Words ending in a vowel (a e i u, not o which maps [u]) or -s endings are paroxytone. Infinitives in -ar/-er/-ir are paroxytone (the final -r is silent in spoken Occitan but syllabified here, so penult_stress_endings must list them explicitly). Written accents (à á è é í ò ó ú) always win. Proparoxytones are rare and always written-accented. Note: o-final words are rare in Oc orthography since o reads [u]; nominal -or/-on are oxytone."
